Cell["\<\
Chapter 6 was another tour de force. I did not go slowly enough through \
Feynman\[CloseCurlyQuote]s arguments to follow them. It was just too much. \
Instead, I assume all of us just skipped straight to his result, which was \
Tables 6-1 and 6-2, and used those to do the problems. Here is Table 6-2:\
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9832595847010317`*^9, 3.9832596856560507`*^9}, {
